The Status for the DebugException was not correctly created (message cannot be
null).
The base exception is a ClassNotLoadedException. It happens because the VM is in
a specific state, and a type on which we have an handle is not loaded yet in the
current class loader (see the javadoc of ClassNotLoadedException).
We shouldn't log anything for in this case. It's not an error, just that the
info we need is not available.
The code which generate this exception is used to generate a 'good' generic name
for array of generic type. The info is not directly send by the VM, not sure if
it's a bug or not.
I removed the exception creation. We just return the name we can create.

JDIReferencType - removed the exception creation.
JavaDetailFormatterManager - added a check, we don't want to log the error for a
ClassNotLoadedException.


